{
  "text": "Serum blood lipids were determined from blood samples collected at 0800 after the subjects had fasted overnight for 12 h. Total cholesterol and triacylglycerol concentrations were determined enzymatically with the use of commercial kits, as described elsewhere [CITATION_1] . HDLcholesterol and LDL-cholesterol concentrations were analyzed after precipitation of LDL in the infranatant fluid with heparin and magnesium chloride [CITATION_2] . The ratio of total cholesterol to HDL cholesterol was also derived as a lipid index of ischemic heart disease risk [CITATION_3] .",
